values:
Hey LJ,
Today I learned that I have an entirely different skill. Photography. The pictures I took were great and I am burning them into a CD so I can bring them home. Here is a few.&nbsp;
Sorry I don't have time I have to interview an idiot. I will come back soon. Bye!

Hey guys,&nbsp; 
I haven't updated for a long time but currently I am at Republic Polytechnic as a student reporter for the Youth Avenue camp. Secretly using com now so will quickly update. I will post pics and update later to caption it.&nbsp; 

Currently in conference room where a blackout has taken over everything. We are all working in the dark, watching Youtube and blasting music in between posting blogs on the company website for people to read. Today was the poo, I (like a newfound friend) plucked up courage to ask the company's chairperson a question in one of those ridiculously scary Q&amp;A sessions. And this was in front of JC, Poly and ITE students.&nbsp;

I was shaking so hard my left leg gave way and I almost fell except I was hanging on for dear life to the seat behind me.&nbsp;

Then we went around to do this and that, interviewing MPs and apparent high level "VIPs". Then we played games in the "rain" where we played with fire literally. But the bathing time was the most interesting.&nbsp;

The bathing facilities were freaking clean for a Singaporean school. It was like I was in a modernized Eton school where all the tiles were marble white and no dirt or bacteria existed. It was gigantic and like a maze. The whole campus is empty so we almost got lost when we were going to bath at the Sports Stadium.&nbsp;
 And now back to the Conference room where everyone is slacking and not only doing work but also wandering off to Youtube or Radio Blog Club to refresh our mind. I love camps where you are considered special so you can stay up using up to date laptops to do the "work" assigned to us.&nbsp;

Well, back tomorrow after slacking. BB
